title: For Sale:  Manufacture Liégeoise d’armes à Feu 10 Gauge Pre-1889 Damascus 30" Side-by-Side Shotgun
postcontent:
This is a Manufacture Liégeoise d’armes à Feu 10 Gauge Pre-1889 Damascus 30" Side-by-Side Shotgun for sale.

The shotgun has engravings on the side plates, butt plate, barrel, trigger guard, hammers, and gold inlays on the barrels. The Damascus steel barrels are the "tiger stripe" pattern. As it is very hard to date old Damascus shotguns, the only means I have to on for a date is a R proof mark under the right barrel which was only used until 1889 and means the barrel did not meet inspection and was reworked on.

Other proof marks include the manufacturer proof ( M L with a crown over it), Liege proof mark for Belgian black powder shotguns/rifles ( ELG with star and encircled), 19.2 diameter proof on right barrel and 19.6 diameter proof on left barrel. There are also two H proof marks on the back locking lugs and two v proof marks (one on the outside of each barrel) which I have yet to identify. Also, "FINE TWIST" is inscribed on the barrel strap - identifying it as Damascus steel.

The stock on the gun is walnut with normal wear and tear for such an old shotgun. The engravings are worn but still very visible and the gold inlay on the barrels are immaculate. There is also patina on the barrels, also a very light amount for such an old gun. There is little to no pitting on any metal part. Unfortunately, there are two cracks, one on each side of the stock, under the hammer; most likely from someone not knowing to cock the hammers before removing the barrels.

All in all, this is a beautiful piece and a great look into history. I would NOT suggest shooting it unless looked at by a gun smith who knows these shotguns.

Contact for more info, pictures, video of the gun, etc.: REDACTED
Price: $1500.00

title: For Sale:  Beware of SCAMMER Gloria Edwards Address: 1362 Ga Hwy 199s Lot 2 East Dublin, Ga 31027
postcontent:
Somebody local (East Dublin, GA) is posting bogus ads on Armslist ETC showing my shop Shamrock Pawn as the transfer agent. 

All guns are very desirable and priced at 40-60% of fair market value. 

They have also provided my complete/correct FFL number to potential buyers. 

This has been going on for 6 or 8 weeks. 

I was made aware of this situation after several potential victims called the shop trying to validate the female seller who's name I didn't recognize. It took a few calls to figure out what was going on because I never get involved in private sales other than facilitating shipping another FFL or the transfer on my end. 

Here's the scammers info as passed on to me by a potential victim. 

Gloria Edwards
Address: 1362 Ga Hwy 199s Lot 2 East Dublin, Ga 31027

I contacted local LEO who seemed somewhat interested and the ATF who seemed mostly disinterested. 

I documented everything to cover my ass if this situation takes a turn for the worse. 

Remember, if it looks to good to be true it's probably a scam. 

td

title: For Sale/Trade:  REMINGTON Model 541-S CUSTOM SPORTER 22 LR NICE!
postcontent:
Some of you may know the Remington 541 S Sporter is a highly sought after rifle, especially one in this condition. Engraved and grooved for scope mounting (drilled and tapped).  High gloss checkered walnut stock. Excellent overall condition with a brilliant metal finish. The bore is bright and clean, the rifling is sharp.  Don’t believe it’s been shot much at all.   
Just so you know, this gun has been modified by a craftsman gunsmith, not a guy with hacksaw.  I bought this gun as it is exactly now.  It’s one of the most beautiful 22 rifles I’ve owned.  I believe the barrel was 24” when it came out in 1972 but was cut down to 20” at some time.  However, as far as I know the 20’ barrel was the way it came from factory originally as custom upgrade.  The barrel crowning wasn’t cut by an amateur for sure – see pic.  The butt plate isn’t original but has a decent Remington plate.  I’m sure it can be made to look like original.  I don't know a lot more about this rifle, other than I had a gunsmith at Fine Guns in Bass Pro evaluate it and he said the custom work was done by a professional.  I’m planning on going to the gun show in Springfield this weekend to see if I can possibly find a better butt plate to fit.  Perhaps the previous owner wanted it customized a little shorter for a youngster to shoot, I don't know.  All I know is that it's a very nice 22 rifle that’s near excellent condition and possibly values at for a lot more than I'm asking.  I just need the cash right now for house projects.  If I don’t get what I thinks it is worth, no problem.  I really would like to hold on to it to give to one of grandchildren someday.  I’m firm on my price.   Will be glad to email you many pictures.
